    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix duplicate CQI PDU handling in UL config request\n\n### Summary\nThe function `oai_nfapi_ul_config_req()` in `nfapi_vnf.c` had a logic error in detecting duplicate CQI PDUs for the same UE. This caused malformed UL configuration requests to be sent to the PNF, leading to NGAP interface handling failures.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_vnf.c`: Fixed the PDU type comparison logic in the duplicate detection loop.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions with multiple UEs reporting CQI, the gNB would send UL configuration requests with duplicate CQI PDUs for the same UE to the PNF. This caused the PNF to reject the requests with error codes, leading to:\n1. RRC connection setup failures\n2. UE attachment failures\n3. Intermittent connectivity issues for affected UEs\n\nThe issue is most reproducible when:\n- Multiple UEs are active in the cell\n- CQI reporting is frequent\n- Network load is moderate to high\n\nSymptoms include error messages in the gNB log about \"Problem, two cqis being sent to a single UE\" and subsequent NGAP procedure failures.\n"
}